{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"32d6514a-09ab-44bb-bd07-345a4a947a14","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**File: `my_app/views.py`**\n\n| Line | Call | Issue |\n|------|------|-------|\n| 3 | `datetime.now()` | Hard-coded static — not injectable or mockable in tests |\n\n**Why it's a problem:** `datetime.now()` couples your view directly to the system clock. In tests you can't control what \"now\" is without monkey-patching.\n\n**Recommended fix (Python/Django):** Use `django.utils.timezone.now` and inject it or mock it with `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\n@patch('my_app.views.timezone.now')\ndef test_index(mock_now):\n    mock_now.return_value = datetime(2026, 1, 1)\n    ...\n```\n\nThis is a small project with only one file and one call site, so the fix is straightforward. Want me to apply it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4fd48129-b336-4bfd-9faf-76fe44bb7e21","outputTokens":284,"requestId":"67C8:163FFF:1B7262F:1EF4BC9:69FD505F"},"id":"dc3fef1d-8f12-46cd-a8cf-817a81791a2e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:54:31.251Z","parentId":"71f41094-d632-47bf-92ec-aa1c98791a78"}
